title: Re: Commander Keens Trek 96!
content:
Looks like yet another one of those coincidences where a shovelware company picks a rank and a word that more or less means "cool" and assumes it's completely original in order to sell their product.

I've seen it many times before, although I seem less credible because I honestly can't think of any off the top of my head.

title: Re: Commander Keens Trek 96!
content:
Shovelware is a term commonly used for either games that are more or less crap made cheaply in a short amount of time that nobody's ever heard of that quickly finds its way into the dollar bin at Wal-mart, or those dollar bin CDs containing hundreds of DOS game demos, many of which being crappy games nobody's ever heard of, many of which promising at least one big, good game which is never on the CD ever.

At least, I think this term applies to both of these. Anyone feel free to correct me if I'm wrong.
